Apr 28 2008 	Good value for money	I stayed in this hotel for two nights in April 2008. Having read the reviews on Tripadvisor I feared the worst. However, the hotels was much better than one would expect based on the reviews posted here. Given the fact that you are in London, the low rates (I payed about 50 pounds per night for a single room) and the excellent location, this is a very good choice. Contrary to the experiences of other reviewers, I did have (very) hot water, my room was rather small but fairly clean and the staff was friendly and helpful. They had a locked luggage room and breakfast was simple indeed, but ok. In my opinion: good value for money, I would certainly recommend this hotel for a stay during a city trip if do not need a lot of luxury.	
