led sister hotel where we found another unprofessional receptionist who told us they weren't even sister hotels and had completely different management and that his hotel could not even be rated with 2 stars. We had asked him if we could stay there both nights then to avoid the change of room the next days. He laughed and said we would be better off changing since the Glendale standard was not comparable to the Ascot standard. We were given a room in the basement, which was horrible!!! It was really a nightmare! The bathroom was not even in the room which we had booked, the sink was tiny, you could not even wash your hand there without making a real mess. The shower was in the middle of the room, so when you took a shower, the whole toilet and floor were wet. The beds were old and broken, there was a window and all you could see was an old dryer stored in front of it. You could not even look out to see if the sun was out or if there was pouring rain. It was really disgusting!!! We went back to the Ascot to file our comlaint. There was another receptionist there by now but the girl was still there as well. They both told us they could not do anything about it and we had to talk to the manager on the next day and that he would be ehre from 7 in the morning. I asked them to give me my money back since I was not willing to pay one penny for such a shabby place and unsatisfying service. Please note: we have both travelled a lot in our lifes, I have seen plenty of hotel rooms, I also have stayed at two hostels in London and both of them were alright, clean, safe and with friendly staff with rooms according to their standard. I have never experienced anything like this.In the end no one could help us. It was in the middle of the night, we tried to find another hotel in the area but all of them were completely booked and it did not really make sense to walk around London in the middle of the night to find a room. So we stayed in our room in the basement. I did not sleep very well, I was always expecting someone to break into the room or some little animal to come out and crawl over me. After a horrible night we got up early to see the manager - who was not there at 7, of course...He did not show up until around 8.30 - they told us to go next door to Maxim's restaurant to have breakfast in the meanwhile. This place was just another nightmare - with the same manager! There were rats outside, there was leftover food on the floor and it was even more disgusting. Talking to the manager did not really help. When we told him we had a problem he said he did not have any time to deal with it and that we should not interfere with his work. Excuse me? So who is the guest now??? He started to yell at us and that he did not have a solution for the problem. It seemed like he had no idea of how to run a hotel and that he never ever heard of the word customer service. I am not very demanding as long as things are ok. I understand things might go wrong sometimes but there are just too many things going wrong at this place. While we tried to come to an agreement with the so called manager of this place, an older man as well as another lady walked to the reception to file a complaint as well. The man had problems with his room and the lady complained about the rats in the breakfast facility. The manager yelled at both of them and told them to leave his hotel. After arguing with him for a while, he told us that he would not have a room for guests like us - we left the place. Before we had to fill in a complaint sheet to reveice the money bach. I will give the case to the credit card company to claim my money back because I am not sure if they will really refund anything at all. We found another hotel in Kensington - after spending Saturday morning arguing with a completely nasty hotel manager and sitting in an internet café to look for another place to stay. We wanted to have a nice, relaxing weekend instead the whole Friday night and Saturday morning were spent dealing with a bunch of problems the Ascot Hotel caused us! Luckily the hotel we then stayed in was wonderful - nice staff, great rooms, customer service, an excellent breakfast. I can only tell you: DO NOT STAY THERE!!! DO NOT BOOK ANYTHING THERE! It is a complete rip off! You want to enjoy your stay and not argue with a yelling hotel manager. Find some other place - there are nicer hotels which are not that expensive in London. Even a cheap hostel is better than this place! Stay away from it, do not loose your money to those people! The authorities should take care of this and I will write to them to see spread the word! If you have stayed there and experienced something similar, please write there as well to save other London tourists from that place and that manager!!!Be aware! This is the worst hotel I have ever stayed in...	
